`{ drop: true }` prevents concurrent task instances from stacking up. The `@tracked throttled` flag blocks re-triggering for 5 seconds after the request completes. Using `finally` ensures the timeout always runs even if the fetch throws, so the throttle always resets. The button's `disabled` attribute checks both `isRunning` and `throttled` to cover the cooldown period after the request finishes.

