ember-concurrency automatically cancels all task instances when the component or service they belong to is destroyed via `willDestroy`. You do not need to call `cancelAll()` yourself. However, explicitly calling it can improve readability and makes the intent clear to other developers. Some teams require it as a code style rule for clarity. It is never harmful — calling `cancelAll()` on an already-completed or already-cancelled task is a no-op.

