For auto-refresh polling, `keepLatest` is the better choice. `restartable` could cancel a fetch mid-flight, causing gaps in data. `keepLatest` lets the current fetch finish, discards any intermediate requests, and then runs the most recent queued perform — ensuring data consistency while still responding to the latest trigger.

