For data that is independent (standings do not depend on top scorers, live matches do not depend on standings), always fetch in parallel with `all()`. Waterfall (sequential await) multiplies latency: if each call takes 200ms, sequential = 600ms, parallel = ~200ms. Use waterfall only when later requests depend on the result of earlier ones (e.g., fetch tournament ID first, then fetch matches for that tournament). The task with `all()` gives one unified `isRunning` state and one `last.error` for the entire dashboard load, which simplifies your template logic.

