With `restartable`, when `matchId` changes and the task is re-performed, JavaScript closures capture the value at the time the task function starts. If you read `this.matchId` before any `await`, a restart captures the old value. Reading `this.matchId` after an `await` point ensures you always get the current value at execution time.

