Glimmer `@args` are live references — they reflect the parent's current value at any point in time. In async tasks, `this.args.X` read after an `await` may return a different value than when the task started. Pass args as task parameters (cleanest) or capture them in a local variable before the first `await` to snapshot their values.

```gjs
