`cancelAll()` cancels all instances of the task, including the one currently calling it. This causes the task to throw a `TaskCancelation` mid-execution, leaving your application in a partially updated state. Handle error conditions with early `return`, by setting `@tracked` error state, or by throwing a descriptive `Error` — not by self-cancelling.

