Route `model()` hooks should return data directly or await a task instance. Starting a task without awaiting it and storing data in `@tracked` means the route renders before data arrives and the tracked property may update after the user has already navigated away. Cancel tasks in `deactivate()` (the route lifecycle hook for leaving a route) to prevent stale-data writes after navigation.

