Ember Data's `record.save()` rejects when the server returns a 422 Unprocessable Entity, but the validation details are stored in `record.errors` (an `Errors` object), not in the rejection reason. After catching the rejection, check `record.errors.length > 0` to distinguish validation failures from network errors. Map `record.errors` to strings for display and re-throw non-validation errors so they surface in `task.last.error`.

