When a task finishes faster than one render frame (~16ms), `isRunning` flips true and back to false before the user perceives it — creating a disorienting flash. Using `Promise.all([actualWork, timeout(MIN_LOADING_MS)])` ensures the spinner displays for at least `MIN_LOADING_MS` milliseconds. This technique is also called "minimum loading state" and is especially important in fast networks where latency is near zero.

