Optimistic updates must be rolled back not only on network errors but also when the task is cancelled (e.g., user navigates away, `restartable` policy fires). Check `err instanceof TaskCancelation` in your `catch` block to rollback the optimistic state before re-throwing. Alternatively, put rollback logic in a `finally` block with a success flag — simpler and guarantees cleanup under all conditions.

