Always reset `@tracked` error state at the beginning of a task run, not at the end. If you clear it only on success, a successful retry after a failure leaves the old error visible until `null` is set, causing a jarring flash of red text followed by green data. Setting `this.error = null` as the first line of the task guarantees the error state is clean before each attempt.

