`maxConcurrency: N` alone does NOT drop excess performs — they are enqueued and will run eventually. This surprises developers who expect drop semantics. Use `{ enqueue: true, maxConcurrency: N }` when you want bounded parallelism with full completion guarantees. Use `{ drop: true }` when you want to silently ignore overlapping requests. Know which semantics you need before choosing.

