`finally` runs regardless of whether a task completed normally, threw an error, or was cancelled. Performing side-effectful tasks (like logging) unconditionally in `finally` means they fire even on explicit cancellation — potentially creating log spam or unintended API calls. Use a `wasCancelled` flag checked via `TaskCancelation` to conditionally run cleanup-only code vs completion code in `finally`.

