`waitForProperty(obj, 'propName', value)` watches the property by string name. A typo creates a silent, infinite hang — no error is thrown, the task just waits forever. Always: (1) spell-check property names, (2) add a development-only assertion that the property exists on the target object, and (3) race `waitForProperty` against a `timeout()` to limit the wait. These three practices together eliminate the silent-hang failure mode.

