Sorting is handled by a reactive getter `sortedStandings` that spreads (to avoid mutating the tracked array) and sorts based on `@tracked sortKey` and `sortDir`. Clicking the same column header toggles direction; clicking a different column sets it as the sort key. The task handles loading/error states while the getter handles display transformation — clean separation of concerns.

