      {{#if this.alertFired}}
        <div class="bg-green-800 text-green-300 text-sm rounded-lg px-3 py-2 mb-3 text-center">
          🚨 Alert fired at {{this.threshold}} runs!
        </div>
      {{/if}}
      {{#if this.isWatching}}
        <button
          class="w-full py-2 bg-red-600 hover:bg-red-700 rounded-lg font-semibold text-sm"
          {{on "click" (perform this.stopAlert)}}
        >Stop Watching</button>
      {{else}}
        <button
          class="w-full py-2 bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 rounded-lg font-semibold text-sm"
          {{on "click" (perform this.pollScore)}}
        >Start Watching</button>
      {{/if}}
    </div>
  </template>
}
```

The `pollScore` task runs an infinite loop with a 5-second `timeout()` between polls. The `alertFired` flag ensures the notification fires only once per threshold crossing. Calling `cancelAll()` on `pollScore` stops the loop cleanly. The threshold input resets `alertFired` so a new alert can trigger if the threshold is changed.

