          <div class="text-green-700 font-semibold text-sm">✅ Dismissal Recorded</div>
          <div class="text-gray-600 text-sm mt-1">{{this.formattedDismissal}}</div>
        </div>
      {{else}}
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-2 mb-4">
          {{#each this.dismissalTypes as |dt|}}
            <button
              class="flex items-center gap-2 px-3 py-2 rounded-xl border-2 text-sm transition-all
                {{if (eq this.dismissalType dt.key)
                  'border-blue-500 bg-blue-50 text-blue-700'
                  'border-gray-200 text-gray-600 hover:border-gray-300'}}"
              {{on "click" (fn this.selectType dt.key)}}
            >{{dt.icon}} {{dt.label}}</button>
          {{/each}}
        </div>
        {{#if this.showFielderInput}}
          <input
            type="text"
            placeholder="Fielder name"
            value={{this.fielder}}
            class="w-full border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-sm mb-4"
            {{on "input" (fn (mut this.fielder) value="target.value")}}
          />
        {{/if}}
        {{#if this.saveError}}
          <div class="text-red-500 text-xs mb-3">{{this.saveError}}</div>
        {{/if}}
        <button
          class="w-full py-2 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded-lg font-semibold disabled:opacity-50 hover:bg-blue-700"
          disabled={{or (not this.dismissalType) this.saveTask.isRunning}}
          {{on "click" (perform this.saveTask)}}
        >
          {{if this.saveTask.isRunning "Saving..." "Record Dismissal"}}
        </button>
      {{/if}}
    </div>
  </template>
}
```

The `formattedDismissal` getter conditionally appends the fielder name for caught, run out, and stumped types, matching the cricket scorecard convention. The fielder input conditionally appears based on `showFielderInput`. Once saved, the form locks and shows the formatted dismissal as confirmation. The `drop` modifier prevents double-recording which would corrupt the scorecard.

