On bell click, `toggleOpen` fires two tasks: one to load the notification list and one to mark all as read. Both are `drop` so rapid clicks don't stack API calls. The badge count goes to 0 optimistically when `markAllRead` runs, and notification objects are updated to `read: true` for visual consistency. The constructor fires `fetchCount` once to populate the badge on initial render.

