The `searchTask` is `restartable` to debounce rapid keystrokes — each new character cancels the previous task. New unique search terms are prepended to `history` and capped at 10 entries. A second `restartable` `saveHistory` task debounces the persistence, so multiple rapid searches only trigger one save. Clicking a history chip re-runs the search and is excluded from re-adding to history since it's already present.

